7: A message for Lord Rolf Zahn!
8:
The Western Brigade confirms that
enemy troops are in retreat! Our
forces are prepared to hound them!
10:
Cat tribe reinforcements have
appeared to face the Eastern
Brigade! Neither side will be able to
take much ground!
12:
But the Southern Brigade has the
worst of it! Ensorcelled storms have
ruined the gunpowder reserves!
15:
Tell the West to abandon their
chase and rendezvous with the East.
The South is to retreat.
19:
Now that they've lost the White Tiger,
they're easy prey! This battle will be
the last!
21:
Victory... Victory for our king! We will
show them the majesty of his cruel
fangs!
27:
Hah, has it already been twenty
years?
28:
Those cats had no options left. And
yet the king would show them no
mercy...
32:
There's been a rebellion! Albert has
sided with the catfolk and deposed
the king!
37:
Thankfully! But there's word that all
diplomatic rights granted to the
cats have been transferred to
Albert...
39:
I never thought I would see the day...
And yet here are.
44: No need. I'll head for the palace.
52:
Rolf Zahn, knight. I've come to
inspect a possible coup d'état.
55:
Lord Zahn, your words are far too
harsh. I may hold power at the
moment, but I've no plans to claim
the throne.
58:
Ah, I see you're the same as ever,
my friend.
59:
You were considerate to come
alone. Your actions have saved
countless lives.
61:
They should be thanking you. I am
merely a general who has lost his
king.
63:
I demand compensation for the
troops. Though they might have
other ambitions, they have served
their country well. I won't see them
forgotten.
66:
Of course. I'll make arrangements to
secure their livelihoods.
68:
Lord Zahn, times are changing.
Dogfolk, catfolk... Soon our
differences will be behind us, and
we walk into the future paw in paw.
70:
Though I fear some would stand
against this future. That's why we'll
still need power to keep the peace.
73:
You are the strongest of our knights;
you paint the battlefield in glory as
an artist covers his canvas. Will you
not lend that talent to our new
kingdom?
76:
Lord Fang, you are not the king.
Though perhaps you should be.
78:
Blood stains my sword, not glory. So
many lives taken, all by decree of
the crown. My actions will still be
fresh in the minds of the people.
79:
If you want to avoid the same mess
as His Majesty, you will take a new
path. Without me.
82:
If it must be this way, then very well.
You leave with my gratitude, Lord
Zahn.
86:
A final warning, Lord Albert: Do not
become a knight who fosters
strength alone. Farewell.
91:
I AM the bloody sword of the king.
Strange as that is to admit.
92:
There is no justice in tyranny; no
peace in revolution. Then I shall be a
sword of loyalty and courage... And
yet, I am still a weapon.
95:
No! That's fool's logic! An excuse to
avoid responsibility!
98:
Though I wore the mask of a noble
sword, I am a cowardly soldier who
could not properly guide his king.
What kind of end do I deserve?
102:
Who gives a rat's ass. I thought I'd
leave you to your grumbling, but
suddenly I wanna see this
bloodthirsty wolf in action.
105:
It's what you want, right? You were
the one who sent me that invitation
for a duel.
109:
Well, I accept your challenge! Bring
it on!
114:
I am the Black Wolf, Rolf Zahn.
Though my sword serves no
master... I will find glory in this match!
120: Hold up... Why are you holding back?
123:
One moment of lost focus and you
landed a blow. As expected of the
White Tiger. The rumors about you
are true.
124:
Come. I offer you my neck... Take
your victory by slaying this
treacherous whelp.
129:
Like hell I will! You think I can't see
straight through this? You better
deal with your own problems!
132:
Follow me! I'm taking you to a place
where you won't spout all this
nonsense ever again!
136:
...What greater shame awaits me?
Will I finally sheath my sword for
good?
137:
Your Highness, if you're out there,
forgive me for my errant loyalty.
